Let's save the user a bit of time
```suggestion
/-- can't be an instance because hM can't be inferred -/
```

By putting it in a namespace, we enable dot notation.
```suggestion
theorem IsTorsionBy.quotient (N : Submodule R M) (r : R)
```
Arguably `r` could be implicit, since it is determined by `h`. I'll leave that choice up to you.
Oops, `r` should definitely be implicit here. Not sure why it isn't. Probably a copy/paste error
